SEO (Search Engine Optimization) Basics
SEO helps your content rank better in search engine results. HTML5 provides several tools to improve SEO:

<title> Tag: Specifies the title of the page, which appears in search engine results. Example:
html
Copy code
<title>My Awesome Website</title>
<meta> Tags: Meta tags provide search engines with information about your page, such as the description or keywords. Example:
html
Copy code
<meta name="description" content="This is an awesome website for learning HTML5.">
Combining Accessibility and SEO
Both accessibility and SEO are improved when you use semantic HTML and provide meaningful descriptions, alternative text for images, and structured content.

<header>
    <h1>Learn HTML5</h1>
    <nav>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="#about" title="Learn about HTML5 basics">About</a></li>
            <li><a href="#contact" title="Contact us for more information">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>
</header>



